00:16:28,422 --> 00:16:31,251
TASHA: Now, tell me what she
does that's so special?

260
00:16:34,254 --> 00:16:37,431
I, um... I doubt she does
anything that you can't do.

261
00:16:37,474 --> 00:16:39,346
Ah, but there is a difference.

262
00:16:40,303 --> 00:16:41,565
What's that?

263
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:44,612
She's afraid. I'm not.

264
00:16:45,656 --> 00:16:47,006
Afraid of what?

265
00:16:48,137 --> 00:16:48,920
Conflict.

266
00:16:50,313 --> 00:16:51,314
And you can't change that.

267
00:16:52,098 --> 00:16:53,055
Why not?

268
00:16:56,145 --> 00:17:00,236
Because... Well, in order
to change Celeste,

269
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:01,672
you have to confront her.

270
00:17:01,716 --> 00:17:05,067
If you confront her,
she'll run away.

271
00:17:05,111 --> 00:17:07,156
She's from Ohio, for God's sake.

272
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:10,594
She grew up milking cows,
playing softball.

273
00:17:10,638 --> 00:17:14,076
She just doesn't understand
people like us.

274
00:17:18,863 --> 00:17:21,083
She moved out here
right after her mom died.

275
00:17:21,127 --> 00:17:23,042
You knew that, right?

276
00:17:23,085 --> 00:17:26,219
Yeah. I guess she just
packed up her bird and left.

277
00:17:26,262 --> 00:17:27,916
That wasn't her bird.
That was her mom's.

278
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:32,268
Whatever. That's just
the way she is.

279
00:17:32,312 --> 00:17:35,924
Something goes wrong
and she runs away.

280
00:17:41,408 --> 00:17:44,063
I think you should let me

281
00:17:46,456 --> 00:17:47,718
take your mind off her.

282
00:17:48,589 --> 00:17:49,633
[LAUGHS SOFTLY]

283
00:17:51,026 --> 00:17:53,028
You're really fun to flirt with.

284
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:54,682
And if things were different,

285
00:17:54,725 --> 00:17:56,988
we could carry this right into the night.
But I just...

286
00:17:57,032 --> 00:17:58,468
But you want someone else.

287
00:18:01,602 --> 00:18:03,125
Story of my life.

288
00:18:03,169 --> 00:18:04,866
It's not that I want her, Tasha.

289
00:18:06,215 --> 00:18:07,695
I never said this
about anyone before,

290
00:18:07,738 --> 00:18:10,872
but, I need her.

291
00:18:17,748 --> 00:18:20,490
Why did you have these
delivered here?

292
00:18:20,534 --> 00:18:23,450
Because the last time
I sent them to the hotel,

293
00:18:23,493 --> 00:18:24,799
they lost them.

294
00:18:24,842 --> 00:18:26,714
Thank you. All right.

295
00:18:26,757 --> 00:18:28,063
Listen, I was thinking
we're gonna have to hire

296
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:31,022
some people to help
us set up the room.

297
00:18:31,066 --> 00:18:34,200
And I had this list here
I wanted to show you.

298
00:18:34,243 --> 00:18:35,505
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

299
00:18:36,202 --> 00:18:38,247
Uh...

300
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:41,120
If that's Brent, can you just
tell him that I'm not here?

301
00:18:41,163 --> 00:18:42,991
Still?

302
00:18:43,034 --> 00:18:44,732
Got to talk to him sometime.

303
00:18:45,863 --> 00:18:47,387
RSVP, Tasha speaking.

304
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:49,084
MAN: May I speak
to Celeste, please?

305
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:50,433
And can I tell her
who's calling?

306
00:18:50,477 --> 00:18:52,043
Yeah, Mike
from Baxter's Jewelers.

307
00:18:52,087 --> 00:18:53,132
Sure, hold on.

308
00:18:54,611 --> 00:18:56,483
Mike, from some jewelry store.

309
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:00,400
This is Celeste. Hi.

310
00:19:00,443 --> 00:19:03,185
Who's this? It's me.

311
00:19:03,229 --> 00:19:05,013
You gave me almost nothing
the other night.

312
00:19:09,539 --> 00:19:10,845
What do you want?

313
00:19:10,888 --> 00:19:12,412
I'll tell you what I've got.

314
00:19:12,455 --> 00:19:15,328
CELESTE OVER RECORDER:
How did you get this number?

315
00:19:15,371 --> 00:19:17,199
Tasha gave it to
you, didn't she?

316
00:19:17,243 --> 00:19:19,897
MAN: I'm just asking you
for a little more.

317
00:19:19,941 --> 00:19:21,725
At night, I turn off
all the lights

318
00:19:21,769 --> 00:19:23,553
and listen to your voice.

319
00:19:23,597 --> 00:19:26,252
I imagine you lying there
in your silky thong.

320
00:19:26,295 --> 00:19:28,123
Running your fingers back and...

321
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:29,820
Listen to me you sick bastard,

322
00:19:29,864 --> 00:19:32,388
you ever call here again,
I'm calling the police.

323
00:19:34,738 --> 00:19:36,914
[BEEPING] [LINE RINGING]

324
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:38,742
OPERATOR:
The number you are calling
has been blocked

325
00:19:38,786 --> 00:19:39,874
and cannot be accessed...

326
00:19:39,917 --> 00:19:41,484
TASHA: Big surprise.

327
00:19:41,528 --> 00:19:43,094
[SIGHS] What do you wanna do,
call the phone company?

328
00:19:43,138 --> 00:19:44,879
Okay, you don't think
that that was Brent?

329
00:19:44,922 --> 00:19:45,967
No.

330
00:19:46,010 --> 00:19:47,795
No. Of course it's not Brent.

331
00:19:47,838 --> 00:19:49,884
Who else could it be?

332
00:19:49,927 --> 00:19:52,452
He knows my name, he knows
where I live, where I work.

333
00:19:52,495 --> 00:19:53,583
Call him. Ask him.

334
00:19:54,932 --> 00:19:56,064
You call him.

335
00:19:57,892 --> 00:19:59,937
It's not Brent.

336
00:19:59,981 --> 00:20:01,243
He said that I wear a thong.

337
00:20:02,810 --> 00:20:04,333
So?

338
00:20:04,377 --> 00:20:06,988
So, Brent is the one
who gave them to me.

339
00:20:10,296 --> 00:20:13,124
[SIGHS] All right, um,
I'll talk to him.

340
00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:16,084
Thanks.

341
00:20:45,940 --> 00:20:48,290
[PHONE RINGING]

342
00:20:48,334 --> 00:20:50,118
CELESTE ON MACHINE:
Hi, uh, I can't come
to the phone right now.

343
00:20:50,161 --> 00:20:51,815
So, leave a message and
I'll call you back. Thanks.

344
00:20:51,859 --> 00:20:53,121
[MACHINE BEEPS]

345
00:20:58,996 --> 00:21:00,737
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

346
00:21:11,618 --> 00:21:13,315
Hello.

347
00:21:13,359 --> 00:21:15,274
MAN: If you hang up,
you'll be sorry.

348
00:21:17,145 --> 00:21:18,320
How did you get this number?

349
00:21:20,148 --> 00:21:22,106
There are three
rules to this game.

350
00:21:22,150 --> 00:21:24,457
First, you can't block
your phone.

351
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,894
Second, you can't call
the police.

352
00:21:26,937 --> 00:21:28,939
Third, you can't have
a boyfriend.

353
00:21:28,983 --> 00:21:31,072
If you break a rule,
you'll be punished.

354
00:21:31,115 --> 00:21:32,552
Any questions?

355
00:21:33,553 --> 00:21:35,337
And I'll be watching you.

356
00:21:35,381 --> 00:21:36,338
Watching?

357
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:06,586
Well, telescopes are pretty
popular in these buildings.

358
00:22:06,629 --> 00:22:08,239
That's why, the first thing
I want you to do

359
00:22:08,283 --> 00:22:09,676
is to cover up all your windows.

360
00:22:09,719 --> 00:22:11,678
Yeah, I was gonna
do that today. Yeah.

361
00:22:11,721 --> 00:22:14,637
And then, you take off
the anonymous call rejection.

362
00:22:14,681 --> 00:22:17,248
But then he can call me.

363
00:22:17,292 --> 00:22:19,512
See, what you need to do
is get yourself a second line.

364
00:22:19,555 --> 00:22:22,166
You keep the number
unpublished and unlisted.

365
00:22:22,210 --> 00:22:23,994
ZAMORA: You give it out
to your closest friends.

366
00:22:24,038 --> 00:22:26,083
That way, he keeps calling
on the first line

367
00:22:26,127 --> 00:22:28,347
thinking he's getting through.
But what he's really doing

368
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:30,174
is giving us more information.

369
00:22:30,218 --> 00:22:32,742
So you can trace his call?

370
00:22:32,786 --> 00:22:34,396
Not if he is calling
from a pay phone

371
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:36,659
or using a calling card.

372
00:22:36,703 --> 00:22:38,574
Those calls are almost
impossible to trace.

373
00:22:38,618 --> 00:22:40,750
But he might give us information

374
00:22:40,794 --> 00:22:42,099
if he leaves messages.

375
00:22:45,842 --> 00:22:47,540
I begged her not to go.

376
00:22:47,583 --> 00:22:49,019
I knew it was a mistake.

377
00:22:49,063 --> 00:22:51,239
What does her moving out
have to do with this?

378
00:22:51,282 --> 00:22:54,285
[BANGS TABLE]
Somebody's stalking her.

379
00:22:54,329 --> 00:22:55,591
That wouldn't happen
if she stayed.

380
00:22:55,635 --> 00:22:57,811
And you think, what,
if she moved back...

381
00:22:57,854 --> 00:22:59,943
Yeah, I think it would stop.

382
00:22:59,987 --> 00:23:01,554
Really?

383
00:23:01,597 --> 00:23:03,251
Well, that could be
a motive right there.

384
00:23:04,339 --> 00:23:05,427
For what?

385
00:23:05,471 --> 00:23:06,210
Scaring her.

386
00:23:11,215 --> 00:23:13,957
You know,
you are either innocent

387
00:23:14,001 --> 00:23:15,350
or you're a really good actor.

388
00:23:18,571 --> 00:23:20,224
Why can't I be both?

389
00:23:33,673 --> 00:23:35,152
Thank you. You are welcome.

390
00:23:40,593 --> 00:23:42,508
He told me
not to call the police.

391
00:23:42,551 --> 00:23:44,684
That's why I waited
till I was at work.

392
00:23:44,727 --> 00:23:46,512
Well, if he's watching, it
might not make a difference.

393
00:23:46,555 --> 00:23:48,209
He could be out there right now.

394
00:23:48,252 --> 00:23:50,733
I know.

395
00:23:50,777 --> 00:23:52,300
[SIGHS]
Where are you going?

396
00:23:52,343 --> 00:23:53,997
CELESTE: I have to pick up the
guest list for the banquet

397
00:23:54,041 --> 00:23:57,436
and, uh, go to the hotel
to check on the space.

398
00:23:57,479 --> 00:23:59,481
And then I have to find
a new place to live.

399
00:23:59,525 --> 00:24:01,004
Well, hang on a second.

400
00:24:01,048 --> 00:24:02,658
If he is following you,

401
00:24:02,702 --> 00:24:04,486
he'll find out where you are
no matter where you live.

402
00:24:04,530 --> 00:24:06,532
Right. But he won't be
able to watch me

403
00:24:06,575 --> 00:24:07,837
through my living room windows.
I'll see you later.

404
00:24:08,795 --> 00:24:09,970
Yeah.

405
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:19,283
Okay. Right.

406
00:24:20,807 --> 00:24:22,417
No, that sounds totally fine.

407
00:24:41,523 --> 00:24:42,611
I need a taxi.

408
00:24:54,101 --> 00:24:55,450
CELESTE: Excuse me.

409
00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:57,017
I'm looking for Glenn Moser.

410
00:24:57,060 --> 00:24:58,409
He's at lunch.

411
00:24:58,453 --> 00:24:59,976
[SIGHS] Do you know
when he'll be back?

412
00:25:00,020 --> 00:25:01,151
Around 1:00.

413
00:25:01,195 --> 00:25:02,457
Right. Do you mind
if I just wait here?

414
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:04,328
No, ma'am. Thanks.

415
00:25:24,305 --> 00:25:25,828
You could look at the lease.

416
00:25:25,872 --> 00:25:27,961
There's nothing in
here about harassment.

417
00:25:29,136 --> 00:25:30,790
Then I'm gonna have to sublet.

418
00:25:30,833 --> 00:25:33,270
There's a clause
in here about that.

419
00:25:33,314 --> 00:25:34,576
Says you can't do it.

420
00:25:36,578 --> 00:25:39,233
All right, can I talk to
the owner of the building?

421
00:25:39,276 --> 00:25:40,495
It's owned by a conglomerate.

422
00:25:42,279 --> 00:25:44,630
Who runs that conglomerate?

423
00:25:44,673 --> 00:25:46,501
They have a board of directors.

424
00:25:46,545 --> 00:25:48,329
And they'll just
send you back to me.

425
00:25:48,372 --> 00:25:50,853
So it's really up to you?

426
00:25:50,897 --> 00:25:52,986
GLENN:
It's up to the contract.

427
00:25:53,029 --> 00:25:55,423
Look, I let a lady out
of her lease last year.

428
00:25:55,466 --> 00:25:57,556
And I almost my job over it.

429
00:25:57,599 --> 00:25:59,688
All right, can you at least find
out if there's an apartment

430
00:25:59,732 --> 00:26:01,211
with a telescope pointing
into my living room?

431
00:26:04,780 --> 00:26:07,261
You know, I've been in
a lot of these units.

432
00:26:07,304 --> 00:26:09,959
And you'd be amazed to see how
many of them have telescopes.

433
00:26:10,003 --> 00:26:11,047
[SCOFFS]

434
00:26:12,222 --> 00:26:14,181
Great. So, um...

435
00:26:14,224 --> 00:26:15,661
Will you please
put up my drapes?

436
00:26:16,836 --> 00:26:17,837
I'm working on it.

437
00:26:19,795 --> 00:26:23,016
And I'll tell security
to keep an eye on things.

438
00:26:23,059 --> 00:26:24,539
It's the best I can do.

439
00:26:27,673 --> 00:26:29,631
[GRUNTS] Maybe I should
just go back to Ohio.

440
00:26:31,328 --> 00:26:32,939
TASHA: Ohio? Hmm?

441
00:26:32,982 --> 00:26:35,550
And what about the lease?

442
00:26:35,594 --> 00:26:36,986
Well, I guess I could always

443
00:26:37,030 --> 00:26:38,597
send them the money
when I have it.

444
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,033
[CLEARS THROAT]

445
00:26:40,076 --> 00:26:42,818
I co-signed for that lease.

446
00:26:42,862 --> 00:26:45,125
Guess who they're
gonna come after.

447
00:26:45,168 --> 00:26:47,214
Yeah.
[SIGHS]

448
00:26:47,257 --> 00:26:49,738
Besides, you know.
Maybe it's good that you're stuck here.

449
00:26:51,784 --> 00:26:53,786
Okay. What do you mean?

450
00:26:53,829 --> 00:26:56,136
I mean... [KITTY SQUAWKS]

451
00:26:56,179 --> 00:26:59,008
You can't keep running
away from everything.

452
00:26:59,052 --> 00:27:01,576
Oh. And I suppose that you would
just throw open the curtains

453
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:03,230
and start dancing
naked for the guy.

454
00:27:04,361 --> 00:27:05,928
I might.

455
00:27:05,972 --> 00:27:08,061
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

456
00:27:08,104 --> 00:27:10,498
But, I know
that what I wouldn't do.

457
00:27:10,541 --> 00:27:11,717
Wouldn't count on
the police to find him.

458
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:14,676
You know what?
Fight back.

459
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:16,852
Right. And how do you do that when
you don't know who you're fighting?

460
00:27:16,896 --> 00:27:18,462
Well, that's the first thing
you gotta do.

461
00:27:19,376 --> 00:27:20,464
Find him.

462
00:27:22,423 --> 00:27:24,294
Okay. How do I find him?

463
00:27:27,689 --> 00:27:29,648
Same way he found you.

464
00:27:31,258 --> 00:27:32,433
Grab your things.

465
00:27:40,180 --> 00:27:42,878
CELESTE: Says here the viewfinder
is a wide-angled sighting scope

466
00:27:42,922 --> 00:27:45,838
with cross-hairs to make it easy to
center objects in the eye-piece.

467
00:27:45,881 --> 00:27:48,014
Well, I'm not having
any trouble centering things.

468
00:27:56,718 --> 00:27:58,720
Mmm.

469
00:27:58,764 --> 00:28:01,462
TASHA: I can see why this
is such a popular sport.

470
00:28:04,726 --> 00:28:07,033
Why you ask?
Well, it's all rather phallic,

471
00:28:07,076 --> 00:28:09,992
isn't it? I mean, this long
sleek tube penetrating

472
00:28:10,036 --> 00:28:12,386
to the most private parts
of people's lives.

473
00:28:14,823 --> 00:28:17,173
TASHA: Mmm.
[CHUCKLES]

474
00:28:17,217 --> 00:28:19,219
CELESTE: Okay, we're not
doing this to spy on people.

475
00:28:19,262 --> 00:28:20,829
TASHA: You're such
a spoilsport.

476
00:28:20,873 --> 00:28:21,830
Mmm-hmm.

477
00:28:24,528 --> 00:28:25,791
TASHA: Okay, I got one.

478
00:28:25,834 --> 00:28:28,097
Room on the 14th floor...

479
00:28:28,141 --> 00:28:29,708
[MUMBLING]

480
00:28:29,751 --> 00:28:31,448
Ninth window from the left.

481
00:28:31,492 --> 00:28:33,712
Can you see anybody?

482
00:28:33,755 --> 00:28:35,626
Um... No. Just the telescope.

483
00:28:37,454 --> 00:28:39,282
[SIGHS] That makes 11.

484
00:28:39,326 --> 00:28:40,544
[GASPS] Oh, my God.

485
00:28:42,329 --> 00:28:43,504
What is it?

486
00:28:43,547 --> 00:28:44,940
Mrs. Tasgrove, butt naked.

487
00:28:46,594 --> 00:28:48,639
I did not need to see that.

488
00:28:48,683 --> 00:28:51,033
All right.
So that makes 11 windows with telescopes...

489
00:28:51,077 --> 00:28:52,295
And then nobody using them.
Now what?

490
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:56,386
Now, we gotta get him
to come to the window.

491
00:28:58,867 --> 00:29:00,173
How?

492
00:29:00,216 --> 00:29:01,087
Give him something to look at.

493
00:29:02,392 --> 00:29:03,567
I'm not taking
these sheets down.

494
00:29:04,786 --> 00:29:06,179
Well... [SCOFFS]

495
00:29:06,222 --> 00:29:07,876
You have to bait the trap.
You know...

496
00:29:07,920 --> 00:29:09,660
Tease them a little.

497
00:29:09,704 --> 00:29:11,445
Hmm. I'm not doing
that either.

498
00:29:12,968 --> 00:29:14,796
[CLICKS TONGUE]
Of course not.

499
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,145
Mmm.

500
00:29:16,189 --> 00:29:19,583
All right. You look
through the telescope.

501
00:29:19,627 --> 00:29:21,063
I'll do my best
to get his attention.

502
00:29:21,847 --> 00:29:22,761
Somehow.

503
00:29:31,421 --> 00:29:33,119
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING] Music.

504
00:29:42,781 --> 00:29:43,782
Lights.

505
00:29:46,872 --> 00:29:48,308
Action.

506
00:29:48,351 --> 00:29:49,613
Done this before?

507
00:30:41,013 --> 00:30:42,275
[PHONE RINGING]

508
00:30:44,364 --> 00:30:46,366
CELESTE ON MACHINE:
Hi, uh, I can't come
to the phone right now.

509
00:30:46,409 --> 00:30:47,846
So, leave a message and
I'll call you back. Thanks.

510
00:30:50,674 --> 00:30:53,112
INSTALLER: Get a lot of
hang-ups on that line, huh?

511
00:30:53,155 --> 00:30:55,375
Yeah. That's why the new
one's gonna be unlisted.

512
00:30:55,418 --> 00:30:57,943
Well, you shouldn't have
any problem with this one.

513
00:30:57,986 --> 00:30:59,422
